        <updateDate>2021-04-08T22:19:37Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>COVID-19 Emergency Telehealth Impact Reporting Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to analyze the impact of expanded Medicare telehealth services that were authorized through emergency waivers related to the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) pandemic. </p> <p>In developing this analysis, HHS must seek input from the Medicare Payment Advisory Commission, the Medicaid and CHIP Payment and Access Commission, and other stakeholders.</p> <p>Additionally, the final report of the analysis must include conclusions about the impact of telehealth on health care delivery and estimates for Medicare spending on telehealth during the COVID-19 emergency.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
